<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="95" pageId="0" pageNumber="92" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,1727,2041]" box="[199,1217,1945,1969]" pageId="0" pageNumber="92">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,514,1945,1969]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="92" reason="1">
Description of the 
<typeStatus box="[409,509,1945,1969]" pageId="0" pageNumber="92">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity box="[658,756,1945,1969]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.52" pageId="0" pageNumber="92" unit="mm" value="9.52">9.52 mm</quantity>
. Colour uniformly cinnamon brown, shiny.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,1727,2041]" pageId="0" pageNumber="92">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,260,1981,2005]" pageId="0" pageNumber="92">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[275,341,1981,2005]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[197,1396,395,1947]" captionTargetId="figure-114@1.[177,1411,374,1954]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Holotype of Bolboceras krikkeni Gupta, Ghosh, Das &amp; Chandra, new species. 1, oblique and lateral habitus view; 2, head, dorsal view; 3-4, pronotum, dorsal view; 5, habitus, lateral view; 6, aedeagus, upper side view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876938" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876938/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="92">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Labrum serrated laterally, anteromedian border straight, a transverse ridge on punctate upper surface distinct. Clypeal surface with supra-anterolateral angles distinctly raised, dentate, intervening ridge concave in axial view,
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,151,355]" pageId="1" pageNumber="93">straight in dorsal view; lateral perimarginal ridges distinct, strongly evenly curved, genal angle distinct. Clypeus and remainder of head surface finely punctate, shining behind interocular ridge. Anterior edge of eye canthus raised to slight anterolateral angle, surface coarsely rugose; paraocular ridge distinct, fine ranging from genal angle, thence arcuate along edge of distal lobe; surface closely rugose; paraocular ridge fine, straight, extending posteriorly along eye. Transverse interocular elevation between posterior part of eyes long, convex, reaching paraocular ridges, crest fine and straight, lateral angle obtuse on either end (axial view).</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876938" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6876938" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876938/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="93" startId="1.[151,264,1977,2001]" targetBox="[197,1396,395,1947]" targetPageId="1">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1977,2038]" pageId="1" pageNumber="93">
