<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1367,2039]" pageId="2" pageNumber="94">
<emphasis box="[199,454,1367,1391]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="94" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1367,1391]" pageId="2" pageNumber="94">Pronotum</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[332,441,1367,1391]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[197,1396,395,1947]" captionTargetId="figure-114@1.[177,1411,374,1954]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Holotype of Bolboceras krikkeni Gupta, Ghosh, Das &amp; Chandra, new species. 1, oblique and lateral habitus view; 2, head, dorsal view; 3-4, pronotum, dorsal view; 5, habitus, lateral view; 6, aedeagus, upper side view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876938" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876938/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="94">Figs. 3, 4</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Pronotum anteromedially steeply declivous, outline of marginate anterior border slightly convex; discoparamedian and discolateral protrusions on pronotum distinctly protuberant, subrectangular (lateral view), their tip pointed; discomedian concavity distinct, evenly concave, small, anterior part situated between discoparamedian tubercles (not continuing over anterior declivity), posterior edge rounded; discolateral concavity deep, posterior edge sinuate; anteriorly, at bottom, delimited by coarsely punctate patch behind eyes; saddle from discoparamedian tubercle to posterior disc short, not lowered; bottom of discal concavities and anterior declivity subsericeous; basomedian surface glossy, with abundantly, finely punctate midline impression; anterolateral angle of marginal pronotal ridge obtuse (dorsal view). Pronotal surface with double punctation, primary punctation (size variable) laterally abundant, denser on anterior declivity; secondary punctation sparse, minute. Pronotal base broadly marginate, lined with black, numerous punctures.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1367,2039]" box="[199,847,1691,1715]" pageId="2" pageNumber="94">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,313,1691,1715]" pageId="2" pageNumber="94">Scutellum</emphasis>
with abundant, double punctuation, apex shining.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1367,2039]" box="[199,906,1727,1751]" pageId="2" pageNumber="94">
<emphasis box="[199,282,1727,1751]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="94" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,275,1727,1751]" pageId="2" pageNumber="94">Venter</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Intercoxal anterior lobe of metasternum trunctate in front.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1367,2039]" pageId="2" pageNumber="94">
<emphasis box="[199,374,1763,1787]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="94" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,272,1763,1787]" pageId="2" pageNumber="94">Elytra</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[291,361,1763,1787]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[197,1396,395,1947]" captionTargetId="figure-114@1.[177,1411,374,1954]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Holotype of Bolboceras krikkeni Gupta, Ghosh, Das &amp; Chandra, new species. 1, oblique and lateral habitus view; 2, head, dorsal view; 3-4, pronotum, dorsal view; 5, habitus, lateral view; 6, aedeagus, upper side view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876938" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876938/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="94">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Discal striae shallowly impressed, finely punctate. Elytral interstriae slightly convex, vaguely, sparsely, punctate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1367,2039]" pageId="2" pageNumber="94">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,252,1835,1859]" pageId="2" pageNumber="94">Legs</emphasis>
. Protibiae with 6 external denticles; apex with slightly toothed, flattened, tapering spur. Outer side of meso- and metatibiae with bilobate apical and one complete anteapical fossorial elevation (their crest fringed with fine spines).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1367,2039]" pageId="2" pageNumber="94">
<emphasis box="[199,405,1907,1931]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="94" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,309,1907,1931]" pageId="2" pageNumber="94">Aedeagus</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[325,392,1907,1931]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[197,1396,395,1947]" captionTargetId="figure-114@1.[177,1411,374,1954]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Holotype of Bolboceras krikkeni Gupta, Ghosh, Das &amp; Chandra, new species. 1, oblique and lateral habitus view; 2, head, dorsal view; 3-4, pronotum, dorsal view; 5, habitus, lateral view; 6, aedeagus, upper side view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876938" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876938/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="94">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Sclerotised lateral stalks broad, slightly elevated medially, tip blunt; parameral sheaths narrow, elongated, externally curved.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1367,2039]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,151,716]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="95" pageId="2" pageNumber="94">
<emphasis box="[199,532,1979,2003]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="94" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,525,1979,2003]" pageId="2" pageNumber="94">Measurements of body parts</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Median length of head (full-face, excluding labrum and mandibles) 
<quantity box="[1266,1364,1979,2003]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.29" pageId="2" pageNumber="94" unit="mm" value="2.29">2.29 mm</quantity>
, width (including eyes) 
<quantity box="[333,433,2015,2039]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.19" pageId="2" pageNumber="94" unit="mm" value="3.19">3.19 mm</quantity>
. Median length of pronotum (dorsal) 
<quantity box="[842,941,2015,2039]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.76" pageId="2" pageNumber="94" unit="mm" value="3.76">3.76 mm</quantity>
, maximum width 
<quantity box="[1138,1238,2015,2039]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.88" pageId="2" pageNumber="94" unit="mm" value="6.88">6.88 mm</quantity>
. Median length of scutellum 
<quantity box="[261,359,151,175]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="95" unit="mm" value="0.95">0.95 mm</quantity>
, maximum width 1.0 mm. Sutural length of elytra (dorsal) 
<quantity box="[988,1085,151,175]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.95" pageId="3" pageNumber="95" unit="mm" value="3.95">3.95 mm</quantity>
, maximum width combined 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.41" pageId="3" pageNumber="95" unit="mm" value="7.41">7.41 mm</quantity>
. Width genital capsule 
<quantity box="[444,542,187,211]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" pageId="3" pageNumber="95" unit="mm" value="1.25">1.25 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,716]" pageId="3" pageNumber="95">
<emphasis box="[199,429,223,247]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="95" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,422,223,247]" pageId="3" pageNumber="95">Sexual dimorphism</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Female (
<figureCitation box="[531,596,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–8. 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1259,1283]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,190,1221]" captionTargetId="figure-20@2.[151,1436,181,1235]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7–8. 7, female paratype of Bolboceras krikkeni Gupta, Ghosh, Das &amp; Chandra, new species; 8, map of India and adjacent countries showing distribution records of Bolboceras inaequale species group." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876940" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876940/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="95">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
) similar to 
<typeStatus box="[723,816,223,247]" pageId="3" pageNumber="95">holotype</typeStatus>
in morphological characters except discoparamedian and discolateral protrusions on pronotum less protuberant.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="95" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,716]" pageId="3" pageNumber="95">
<emphasis box="[199,329,296,320]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="95" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,296,320]" pageId="3" pageNumber="95">Etymology</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Named after Dr Jan Krikken, Leiden, 
<collectingCountry box="[739,910,295,319]" name="Netherlands" pageId="3" pageNumber="95">the Netherlands</collectingCountry>
, for his immense contribution to the taxonomy of the subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mulsant" authorityYear="1842" box="[304,465,331,355]" pageId="3" pageNumber="95" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Bolboceratinae">Bolboceratinae</taxonomicName>
of the Oriental Region.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="95" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,716]" pageId="3" pageNumber="95">
<emphasis box="[199,435,367,392]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="95" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,367,391]" pageId="3" pageNumber="95">Distribution</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[355,421,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–8. 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1259,1283]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,190,1221]" captionTargetId="figure-20@2.[151,1436,181,1235]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7–8. 7, female paratype of Bolboceras krikkeni Gupta, Ghosh, Das &amp; Chandra, new species; 8, map of India and adjacent countries showing distribution records of Bolboceras inaequale species group." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876940" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876940/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="95">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[687,733,368,392]" pageId="3" pageNumber="95">type</typeStatus>
locality, Kachchh, Narayan Sarovar Wildlife Sanctuary, 
<collectingRegion box="[1350,1433,367,391]" country="India" name="Gujarat" pageId="3" pageNumber="95">Gujarat</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,209,403,427]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="95">India</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="95" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,716]" pageId="3" pageNumber="95">
<emphasis box="[199,453,439,463]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="95" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,446,439,463]" pageId="3" pageNumber="95">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Gupta, Ghosh, Das &amp; Chandra" authorityName="Gupta, Ghosh, Das &amp; Chandra" authorityYear="2022" box="[464,1035,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Bolboceratidae" genus="Bolboceras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="krikkeni" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[464,682,439,463]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="95">Bolboceras krikkeni</emphasis>
Gupta, Ghosh, Das &amp; Chandra
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1048,1183,439,463]" pageId="3" pageNumber="95" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, can be separated from the other species in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1848" box="[411,548,475,499]" class="Insecta" family="Bolboceratidae" genus="Bolboceras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inaequale">
<emphasis box="[411,548,475,499]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="95">B. inaequale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group by the unique structure of the aedeagus. Morphologically, the new species resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Krikken" authorityYear="2013" box="[348,481,512,535]" class="Insecta" family="Bolboceratidae" genus="Bolboceras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orissicum">
<emphasis box="[348,481,512,535]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="95">B. orissicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in pronotal ornamentation. In 
<taxonomicName authority="Gupta, Ghosh, Das &amp; Chandra" authorityName="Gupta, Ghosh, Das &amp; Chandra" authorityYear="2022" box="[804,1253,511,536]" class="Insecta" family="Bolboceratidae" genus="Bolboceras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="krikkeni" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[804,919,511,535]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="95">B. krikkeni</emphasis>
Gupta, Ghosh, Das &amp; Chandra
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1263,1394,511,535]" pageId="3" pageNumber="95" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, the lateral aedeagal stalks are broad, slightly elevated medially with tip blunt and parameral sheaths are elongated, apically rounded, and somewhat curved outwardly. Whereas, in 
<emphasis box="[768,911,584,607]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="95">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Krikken" authorityYear="2013" box="[768,907,584,607]" class="Insecta" family="Bolboceratidae" genus="Bolboceras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orissicum">B. orissicum</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
the lateral aedeagal stalks are somewhat broad with a recurved hooked tip, and parameral sheaths are narrow and acuminate (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Krikken, J." box="[1044,1210,619,643]" pageId="3" pageNumber="95" pagination="55 - 66" refId="ref2588" refString="Krikken, J. (2013 b) Distinguishing Bolboceras inaequale Westwood, 1848 and two new relatives from India (Coleoptera, Geotrupidae, Bolboceratinae). ZooKeys, 276, 55 - 66." type="journal article" year="2013">Krikken 2013b</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 14). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Krikken" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Bolboceratidae" genus="Bolboceras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="duplicatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="95">Bolboceras duplicatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the new species in the absence of lateral aedeagal stalks, and parameral sheaths are blunt and membraneous (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Krikken, J." box="[357,522,691,715]" pageId="3" pageNumber="95" pagination="55 - 66" refId="ref2588" refString="Krikken, J. (2013 b) Distinguishing Bolboceras inaequale Westwood, 1848 and two new relatives from India (Coleoptera, Geotrupidae, Bolboceratinae). ZooKeys, 276, 55 - 66." type="journal article" year="2013">Krikken 2013b</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 15).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
